# Risk Assessment Methodology

## Purpose

This project uses a fictional Atlanta Falcons case study to demonstrate ISO 27001:2022 risk management practices.

## Risk Identification Process

Risks were identified using the following methodology:

Asset + Threat + Vulnerability = Risk Scenario

## Risk Scoring Method

### Likelihood Scale

| Score | Definition |
|---------|---------|
| 1 | Rare |
| 2 | Unlikely |
| 3 | Possible |
| 4 | Likely |
| 5 | Almost Certain |

### Impact Scale

| Score | Definition |
|---------|---------|
| 1 | Negligible |
| 2 | Minor |
| 3 | Moderate |
| 4 | Major |
| 5 | Severe |

## Risk Formula

Risk Score = Likelihood × Impact

## Risk Ratings

| Score Range | Rating |
|---------|---------|
| 1-4 | Low |
| 5-9 | Medium |
| 10-15 | High |
| 16-25 | Critical |

## Disclaimer

This project is a fictional educational case study and does not represent the actual security posture of the Atlanta Falcons organization.
